thread.title: Most compelling photos from Daytona XFINITY Series season opener
thread.title_full: Most compelling photos from Daytona XFINITY Series season opener

title: Most compelling photos from Daytona XFINITY Series season opener
text:
Feb 25, 2017 at 6:00p ET 0 
It was a wreck-filled NASCAR XFINITY Series season opener Saturday afternoon at Daytona International Speedway. 
Check out the best photos from the Powershares QQQ 300 at Daytona: 
Ryan Reed (left) started on the outside pole alongside Brandon Jones for Saturday's XFINITY season-opening race. 
Richard Childress Racing driver Ty Dillon and wife, Haley, pose for a photo on pit road before he climbed into the No. 3 Chevrolet Camaro. 
Chip Ganassi Racing driver Brennan Poole climbs into his No. 48 Chevrolet Camaro. Poole is sporting a cool-looking Star Wars-themed helmet for the 2017 season. 
Brandon Jones (33) and Ryan Reed (16) lead the field to the green flag. 
Benny Gordon's pit crew makes repairs on the No. 44 after hitting the wall in Turn 2. 
Garrett Smithley (0) spins on the backstretch after Scott Lagasse turned Tyler Reddick, triggering a 19-car melee. A lengthy red-flag period ensued. AP 
Spencer Gallagher (23) gets hit by Stewart-Haas Racing driver Cole Custer during the 19-car pileup. 
Garrett Smithley (0) spins through the grass as Aric Almirola loses control of his No. 98 Ford Mustang. Brendan Gaughan (62) narrowly avoided hitting Almirola. AP 
Brad Keselowski (22) spins while others try to evade the incident. Keselowski got throught the wreck without any major damage. AP 
Cole Custer walks away from his destroyed No. 00 Stewart-Haas Racing Ford Mustang after wrecking in the organization's first XFINITY Series race. 
Brandon Jones (33) and Justin Allgaier (7) hit the Turn 4 wall extremely hard after getting the worst end of a nine-car wreck triggered by Daniel Hemric in the No. 21 Richard Childress Racing Chevy. Erik Jones in the No. 20 Joe Gibbs Racing Toyota was also involved in the crash. 
Bubba Wallace (6) and Daniel Suarez (18) along with Jones (33) as others try to avoid them. The wreck brought out the second lengthy red-flag period of the race before the completion of Stage 1.
